{"author":{"id":"69a73b59e8bca0653e9174a374f9f55c998c9a49750b37bad6bd3960e96b7ca3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1634596982,"nonce":"X8GQPfIskf4/x0jKIe2kwvxxVgc=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDODBZtRc49X35z","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/805","origin":"github"},"title":"Replace auto with GitHub's automatically generated release notes?","message":"GitHub [recently added](https://github.blog/2021-10-04-beta-github-releases-improving-release-experience/#introducing-auto-generated-release-notes) the ability to automatically generate release notes when creating a release, which could theoretically almost entirely replace auto.  We'd just need a new GitHub Actions workflow that creates a tag, creates a GitHub release with autogenerated release notes using the GitHub API, and builds \u0026 uploads the project to PyPI.  The only problem would be triggering the workflow; the best option I can think of is to make the workflow manually triggered via a workflow dispatch event, but no matter what we pick, it seems we'd lose auto's ability to autodetermine the new version.","files":null}]}